The paper proposes a deep learning approach for simplifying the registration problem of brain MR images. This involves training a morphological simplification network (MS-Net) to generate a "simple" image with less anatomical details based on the "complex" input. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with image processing and analysis. Additionally, the use of deep learning models for image simplification and registration suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals specifically with brain MR images, which suggests that it may also belong to the medical imaging (cs.MM) sub-category.
